Should ANC national bosses decide against nullifying the Eastern Cape conference where delegates were injured when a fight over credentials broke out at the East London ICC, lawyer Mvuzo Notyesi will drag the party to court. Notyesi, who gave President Jacob Zuma and his ANC executive at Luthuli House until last Thursday to nullify the conference or face a court case, said he had been instructed to hold off on filing the papers. This was because his clients said they first wanted the ANC to deal with the matter internally before going to court. “For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions”. Tuesday is set aside for the the Mthatha High Court to hear an application for leave to appeal against the dismissal of a case brought by disgruntled OR Tambo ANC members who wanted the party’s 2015 regional elective conference nullified. Mvuzo Notyesi of Mvuzo Notyesi, who is representing ANC member… October 12, 2017 In "Featured" Mthatha-based Lawyer Mvuzo Notyesi has extended the ultimatum given to ANC big bosses in Luthuli House to nullify the recently-held Eastern Cape provincial conference until Thursday. This after the party asked Notyesi for further details on ANC members he's representing after he had initially threatened the party's NEC to nullify… October 10, 2017 In "Featured" The ANC in Eastern Cape may have to shelve its elective conference due in two weeks if the Mthatha High Court nullifies the outcome of the 2015 O R Tambo regional elective conference. The case scheduled for tomorrow will see well-known Mthatha lawyer Mvuzo Notyesi – who represented Winnie Madikizela-Mandela… September 13, 2017 In "Featured"